com.jfoenix.controls

Class JFXToggleNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • javafx.scene.Parent
        • javafx.scene.layout.Region
          • javafx.scene.control.Control
            • javafx.scene.control.Labeled
              • javafx.scene.control.ButtonBase
                • javafx.scene.control.ToggleButton
                  • com.jfoenix.controls.JFXToggleNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget, javafx.scene.control.Skinnable, javafx.scene.control.Toggle

    @DefaultProperty(value="graphic")
public class JFXToggleNode
extends javafx.scene.control.ToggleButton
    JFX Toggle Node , allows any node set as its graphic to be toggled not that JFXToggleNode background color MUST match the unselected color property, else the toggle animation will not be consistent. Notice that the default value for unselected color is set to transparent color.
    Since:
    2016-03-09
